            "command": "git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nFix multi-commodity balance to amount conversion in get_commodity (#763)\n\nWhen a register report uses -H together with a display filter that\nreferences `commodity` (e.g., -d \"commodity == 'EUR'\") on a journal\ncontaining multiple commodities, get_commodity() in src/post.cc was\ncalled for a posting whose compound value was a multi-commodity balance\nand tried to convert that balance to an amount, throwing \"Cannot convert\na balance with multiple commodities to an amount\".\n\nThe existing sequence guard (added for issue #2247) only handled\nis_sequence() and missed the balance-with-many-commodities case.  Extend\nboth get_commodity() and the parallel get_commodity_is_primary() so that\nwhen the compound value is a multi-commodity balance we fall back to\npost.amount's commodity — which matches what a -l filter already sees\nand reflects the posting's semantic commodity.\n\nMove the confirmation test from test/todo/763.test to test/regress/763.test\nwith a scenario that actually exercises this code path (annotated stock\ncommodity plus an expression-based EUR amount under -H, with -l and -d\ncommodity filters).  The test fails with \"Cannot convert a balance with\nmultiple commodities to an amount\" against the unpatched get_commodity\nand passes with the fix.\n\nCloses #763\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -40",
